headline: Democrats Want to Extend Obamacare Subsidies. What That Means for Centene, Tenet, and Other Stocks.
summary: Ever since President Donald Trump won a return ticket to the White House last November, investors have been anticipating the end of federal subsidies that have slashed the prices of health insurance premiums for millions of Americans.  Insurers like  Centene  and  Oscar Health  were bracing for major drops in enrollment in the plans they sell on the ACA exchanges, and hospital companies like  HCA Healthcare  and  Tenet Healthcare  were expecting to treat fewer patients.
